Pseudo-in situ and ex situ EXAFS (Figs. 4 and 5

                           ) suggest that Pd atoms have successfully galvanically replaced the Cu atoms on the nanoparticles while remaining atomically dispersed, confirming the formation of the single-atom catalysts. The tabulated (Table 2
                           ) first shell Pd-Cu bond lengths for the reduced Pd1Cu53 and Pd1Cu216 catalysts were found to be 2.562 ± 0.011 Å and 2.551 ± 0.015 Å, which coincides with a Cu-Cu bond (2.551 ± 0.054 Å).
